.Sh NOTES
libluksde supports both UTF-8 and UTF-16 encoded strings except for filenames.
Some platforms like WINAPI require wide character support for Unicode filenames.
To compile libluksde with wide character support use
.Ar ./configure --enable-wide-character-type=yes
or pass the definition
.Ar _UNICODE
 or
.Ar UNICODE
 to the compiler (i.e. in case of Microsoft Visual Studio (MSVS) C++).

To have other code to determine if libluksde was compiled with wide character support it defines
.Ar LIBLUKSDE_HAVE_WIDE_CHARACTER_TYPE
 in libluksde/features.h.

libluksde allows to be compiled with chained IO support using libbfio.
libluksde will automatically detect if a compatible version of libbfio is available.

To have other code to determine if libluksde was compiled with libbfio support it defines
.Ar LIBLUKSDE_HAVE_BFIO
 in libluksde/features.h.

